<h2> This is a Job page </h2>
My friend  Shan Xu creat this page to help each other
ing a job. <blink><!WA7><a href = "http://www.cs.bgsu.edu/~xtian/job.html"> Job Page </blink></a>Enjoy your job hunting.
<p>
<!WA8><img src="http://www.cs.bgsu.edu/~xtian/ball.gif">
People chat and exchange ideas in Chinese in the news group <!WA9><a href = 
"news:alt.chinese.text"> alt.chinese.text</a>.  Lots of interesting 
debates are going on.  Some good articles are occationally seen.
<p>
<!WA10><img src = "http://www.cs.bgsu.edu/~xtian/ball.gif"> The Montreal Chinese Computer Users Club 
maintains a 
very good <!WA11><a href ="gopher://sunrise.cc.mcgill.ca"> Chinese gopher 
server</a>. 
You can find almost all online magzines in Chinese.  Some novels and peoms
are also worth reading.
<p>
<!WA12><img src = "http://www.cs.bgsu.edu/~xtian/ball.gif"> 
There are currently two WWW servers in mainland China. <!WA13><a href =
"http://www.ihep.ac.cn/china.html"> Institute
of High Energy Physics (IHEP)</a> is the first internet gateway and is
still the most reliable server in China. The other one is at <!WA14><a
href="http://www.cs.bgsu.edu/~xtian/email.html"> E-MAIL ME</a>. 

<p> 
<!WA15><img src = "http://www.cs.bgsu.edu/~xtian/ball.gif"> 
Chinese software, tools and archive for alt.chinese.text can be found at <!WA16><a 
href = "gopher://ifcss.org"> ifcss.org</a>.
<p>
<!WA17><img src = "http://www.cs.bgsu.edu/~xtian/ball.gif">
 <!WA18><a href = 
"ftp://sunsite.unc.edu/pub/multimedia/chinese-music"> Chinese Music</a> 
 is available in both traditional and modern.
<p>
<!WA19><img src = "http://www.cs.bgsu.edu/~xtian/ball.gif"> 
Here is a catalog for <!WA20><a href = "http://peacock.tnjc.edu.tw/ROC_sites.html"> 
WWW servers</a> and <!WA21><a href = "http://www.nctu.edu.tw/nctu_gopher.html"> 
Gopher servers</a> in Taiwan. 
